{"lemma":"كَنِيسَةٍ","slug":"كَنِيسَةٍ","root":"ك.ن.س","root_slug":"ك-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37302"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"church (building and organization)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"synagogue (building and organization)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of palanquin or litter in which the rider conceals himself","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ك ن س (k n s), referring to congregation and sweeping together. Compare the Hebrew root כ־נ־ס (k-n-s), whence Hebrew כְּנֶסֶת (knéset). Apparently, however, the sense of synagogue is a semantic loan from Aramaic כְּנִישְׁתָּא (kənīštā), כְּנִישָׁא (kənīšā), from the root כ־נ־שׁ (k-n-š), to which the Christian sense was added later."},"ipa":["/ka.niː.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37302","headword_ar":"كَنِيسَةٌ","root":"kns","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of worship"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Christians;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Christian church:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Jews;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Jews only:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Jewish synagogue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] that of Christians being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyEapN","text_ar":"بِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh:) [Chald"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"כְנישָׁה","text_ar":"כְנישָׁה","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Golius:)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) being sometimes applied to the former [in classical times, as it is in the present day, as well as to the latter]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of unbelievers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) absolutely: (TA:) an arabicized word, [from the Chaldee mentioned above, or] from [the Persian word]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunisoto","text_ar":"كُنِسْتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Mgh) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanasoto","text_ar":"كَنَسْتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [signifying “ a firetemple ”]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanaAy^isu","text_ar":"كَنَايِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing resembling"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of camel-litter called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawodaj","text_ar":"هَوْدَج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composed of twigs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches, stuck in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHomil","text_ar":"مَحْمِل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a cloth thrown over them, in which the rider sits in the shade and conceals himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylapN","text_ar":"فَعِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunuwsN","text_ar":"كُنُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanasa","text_ar":"كَنَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) pl. as above. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","Sgh","Golius","Msb","TA","Az","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}